text: In contrast to parvoviral enteritis in dogs , estimated to cause 20 , 000 cases per year in Australia , clinical cases of FPL have rarely been diagnosed in Australia since the mid - 1970s , and there have been no reports of FPL outbreaks for over 40 years [ 9 ] . In 2014 , FPL re - emerged in eastern Australia , and subsequent outbreaks occurred between 2015 and 2018 in several locations in this region . Similarly , outbreaks of FPL occurred in New Zealand ( NZ ) between 2016 and 2018 , as well as in the United Arab Emirates ( UAE ) in 2017 , with no outbreaks of FPL reported in either country in recent decades , likely due to the widespread use of FPL vaccines .
